DIRECTOR-General, Lagos State Safety Commission, Mr Lanre Mojola, has decried the activities of unscrupulous members of the public carrying out unlawful activities on behalf of Commission. Mojola expressed this concern while addressing members of staff on the need to take punitive measures against touts parading themselves as staff of the Safety Commission. The Commission’s boss said this on Thursday in a statement made available to newsmen by his office, even as he affirmed the commitment of Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu led administration to the safety of lives and property. ALSO READ:  BREAKING: Lagos PDP elects new executive despite restraining court… El-Rufai’s apology: APC admission of Bello’s failure ― PDP How TB Joshua brokered peace in South Sudan, Tanzania Busola Dakolo to appeal case after court dismisses suit… Southwest development bill scales first reading According to him, “Lagos State Safety Commission hereby dissociates herself from such persons who have branded their vehicles, forged the commission’s official letter headed paper, Abatement Notices and some paraphernalia worn by officials of Lagos State Commission.” He advised members of the public to disregard any illegal purported summons, abatement notices, seal order, saying the Commission was currently undergoing restructuring aimed at repositioning herself for improved service delivery in line with the Commission’ Law Y2011. Mojola warned that anyone found using the Commission’s logo to carry out unofficial duties would be arrested and prosecuted in line with relevant laws of Lagos State as security personnel had been contracted to carry out such directives. He urged members of the public to channel their complaints and enquiries to Lagos State Safety Commission, at the Secretariat, Alausa Ikeja. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
